Also available via anonymous ftp atEven the uninitiated will know that Quantum Field Theory cannot be introducedsystematically in just four lectures. I try to give a reasonably connectedoutline of part of it, from second quantization to the path-integral techniquein Euclidean space, where there is an immediate connection with the rules forFeynman diagrams and the partition function of Statistical Mechanics.